 # Secrets — never commit
.env

# Database — too large, regenerate with run_ingestion.py
*.db

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/

# Jupyter
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# IDE
.vscode/settings.json
.idea/
Save it (Ctrl + S), then commit:
cmdgit add .gitignore
git commit -m "Add .gitignore to protect .env and database"
git push
Then run git status to confirm — .env and energy_grid.db should not appear in the list. Paste the output here if you're unsure.
